Here‚Äôs a clean, restored version of a index-v2.html page that performs a Prebid auction using a synthetic bidder and rotates through a local ads/ folder of creatives. This version removes references to external bidders like AppNexus and ensures the pbjs object is properly defined.

‚úÖ Assumptions:

  • Prebid.js is bundled locally or loaded from CDN.

  • You have an ads/ folder with HTML/JS creative files named like ad1.html, ad2.html, etc.

  • The synthetic bids are hardcoded with CPM values and creative IDs.

‚úÖ Restored index-v2.html

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Prebid Synthetic Bidder Demo</title>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/prebid.js@latest/dist/prebid.js"></script>
  <style>
    #ad-slot {
      width: 300px;
      height: 250px;
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Prebid Synthetic Bidder Demo</h1>
  <button onclick="runAdAuction()">Run Auction</button>
  <div id="ad-slot"></div>

  <script>
    // Define the ad units
    const adUnits = [{
      code: 'ad-slot',
      mediaTypes: {
        banner: {
          sizes: [[300, 250]]
        }
      },
      bids: [{
        bidder: 'syntheticBidder'
      }]
    }];

    // Define synthetic creatives
    const creatives = [
      'ads/ad1.html',
      'ads/ad2.html',
      'ads/ad3.html'
    ];

    // Register the synthetic bidder
    pbjs = window.pbjs = window.pbjs || {};
    pbjs.que = pbjs.que || [];

    // Define synthetic bidder
    pbjs.bidderRegistry = pbjs.bidderRegistry || {};
    pbjs.bidderRegistry.syntheticBidder = {
      callBids: function (bidRequest) {
        bidRequest.bids.forEach((bid, index) => {
          const cpm = (Math.random() * 2 + 1).toFixed(2); // $1.00‚Äì$3.00 CPM
          const creativeIndex = index % creatives.length;
          const adUrl = creatives[creativeIndex];

          const bidResponse = {
            requestId: bid.bidId,
            cpm: parseFloat(cpm),
            width: 300,
            height: 250,
            adUrl: adUrl,
            currency: 'USD',
            creativeId: 'synthetic-' + creativeIndex,
            netRevenue: true,
            ttl: 60,
            ad: `<iframe src="${adUrl}" width="300" height="250" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>`
          };

          pbjs.addBidResponse(bid.placementCode, bidResponse);
        });
        pbjs.bidsBackCallback && pbjs.bidsBackCallback();
      }
    };

    function runAdAuction() {
      pbjs.que.push(() => {
        pbjs.addAdUnits(adUnits);
        pbjs.requestBids({
          bidsBackHandler: function () {
            pbjs.renderAd(document.getElementById('ad-slot'), pbjs.getHighestCpmBids('ad-slot')[0].adId);
          },
          timeout: 700
        });
      });
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>

‚úÖ What This Does:

  • Sets up one ad unit (#ad-slot)

  • Uses a synthetic bidder that creates fake bids with CPMs and rotates creatives

  • Loads creatives from ads/adX.html

  • Renders the winning bid as an <iframe> into the ad slot

  2. Serve via a local HTTP server (e.g. python3 -m http.server).

üîç Root Cause: Generic Analytics Events Are Not Being Sent to Your Server

Your setup correctly defines the analytics adapter (genericAnalyticsAdapter.js) and sets up logging to /collect, but the events are not being POSTed from the browser.

Let‚Äôs walk through the relevant flow to confirm and fix.

‚úÖ Current Working Parts

  1. Analytics server (server.mjs)

    • Accepts POSTs to /collect and appends to a log file.

    • GET /events correctly reads recent events from that log.

    • Aggregates only events of type "lift_auction"server.

  2. Generic Analytics Adapter (genericAnalyticsAdapter.js)

    • Stores labels globally (window.pbjs._analyticsLabels) and prints events to console.loggenericAnalyticsAdapter.

  3. Prebid Setup (index.html)

    • Uses a ?analytics=http://localhost:9090/collect query param to specify endpoint.

    • The analytics(event) function is defined and called in several places (e.g., prebid_init, synthetic_bid, etc.)index.

üö´ What‚Äôs Missing

The analytics() function attempts to send events via navigator.sendBeacon() or fetch():

js
if (ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT) {
  const body = new Blob([JSON.stringify(line)], { type: 'application/json' });
  if (!navigator.sendBeacon || !navigator.sendBeacon(ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT, body)) {
    fetch(ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT, { method: 'POST', mode: 'no-cors', body });
  }
}

But here's the issue:

‚ùå navigator.sendBeacon() is likely failing silently

  • It expects a string or ArrayBufferView, not a Blob.

  • When it fails, it falls back to fetch() with mode: 'no-cors', which also suppresses errors and drops the body if it's not CORS-compliant.

‚úÖ Fix Options

Option 1: Use fetch() with mode: 'cors' and send JSON string

Modify your analytics() function like this:

js
if (ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT) {
  try {
    const body = JSON.stringify(line);

    fetch(ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      mode: 'cors', // allow proper POSTing
      body
    });
  } catch (e) {
    console.warn('analytics send failed', e);
  }
}

Make sure your server sets proper CORS headers (it already does via cors(res) in server.mjs).

Option 2: Modify navigator.sendBeacon() call to use string

You could try:

js
navigator.sendBeacon(ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT, JSON.stringify(line));

But sendBeacon only works reliably with strings or ArrayBufferView, and not all browsers support JSON blobs well here.

‚úÖ Additional Debugging Suggestions

  1. Add server-side logging in /collect

    js
    console.log('Received events:', items);

  2. Use DevTools ‚Üí Network tab

    • Look for POST /collect

    • Check request payload

    • Look for CORS errors

  3. Log errors in the browser
    Modify analytics() to show errors:

    js
    fetch(ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT, {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  mode: 'cors',
  body
}).catch(err => console.error('Fetch error:', err));

‚úÖ Recap of Required Changes

  1. Fix the analytics() network logic:

    • Avoid Blob if using sendBeacon.

    • Or prefer fetch() with proper headers and mode: 'cors'.

  2. Ensure server CORS headers are set (‚úÖ already done).

  3. Use DevTools to verify requests hit /collect.

3) Replace your adapter file with this drop-in

Your current genericAnalyticsAdapter.js just logs to console and stores labels; update it so it POSTs to your server and hoists labels like your server expects:

html
<!-- genericAnalyticsAdapter.js -->
<script>
(function (window) {
  function send(url, payload) {
    try {
      const data = JSON.stringify(payload);
      if (navigator.sendBeacon && navigator.sendBeacon(url, new Blob([data], { type: 'application/json' }))) {
        return;
      }
      // Fallback avoids CORS preflight
      fetch(url, { method: 'POST', mode: 'no-cors', body: data });
    } catch (e) {
      console.warn('[generic] send failed', e);
    }
  }

  function GenericAnalyticsAdapter() {
    var opts = { url: '', batchSize: 1, batchDelay: 100 };
    var q = [], timer = null;

    function flush(force) {
      if (!opts.url || !q.length) return;
      const take = force ? q.splice(0, q.length) : q.splice(0, opts.batchSize);
      send(opts.url, take.length === 1 ? take[0] : take);
      if (q.length) schedule();
    }
    function schedule() { clearTimeout(timer); timer = setTimeout(() => flush(false), opts.batchDelay); }

    return {
      enableAnalytics: function (config) {
        // Prebid calls enableAnalytics({ provider:'generic', options:{...} })
        opts = Object.assign(opts, config && (config.options || config));
        console.log('[generic] enabled', opts);
      },
      track: function (evt) {
        // evt = { eventType, args }
        const labels = (evt && evt.args && evt.args.labels) || {};
        const payload = Object.assign({ labels }, evt);
        q.push(payload);
        if (opts.batchSize <= 1) flush(true); else schedule();
      }
    };
  }

  window.GenericAnalyticsAdapter = GenericAnalyticsAdapter;
})(window);
</script>

Now open your page with e.g.:

bash
http://enrichment-lift:8080/?pbjs_debug=true&ga=http://localhost:9090/collect&synthWinRate=0.9

You should start seeing events at /events?n=20 (auctionInit / bidRequested / bidResponse / auctionEnd / bidWon etc). Because enrichment-lift writes to analytics labels, those labels will appear in the payloads your server logs. Prebid+1

1) genericAnalyticsAdapter.js ‚Äî make it a real Prebid analytics adapter that POSTs

Replace the file contents with this drop-in adapter:

html
<!-- genericAnalyticsAdapter.js -->
<script>
(function (w) {
  function GenericAnalyticsAdapter() {
    var opts = { url: '', batchSize: 5, batchDelay: 200 };
    var q = [], timer = null;

    function sendBatch(items) {
      if (!opts.url || !items.length) return;
      try {
        const json = items.length === 1 ? JSON.stringify(items[0]) : JSON.stringify(items);

        // Try sendBeacon first
        if (navigator.sendBeacon) {
          const ok = navigator.sendBeacon(opts.url, new Blob([json], { type: 'application/json' }));
          if (ok) return;
        }
        // Fallback to fetch with CORS + JSON
        fetch(opts.url, {
          method: 'POST',
          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
          mode: 'cors',
          body: json
        }).catch(() => {});
      } catch (e) {
        console.warn('[generic] send failed', e);
      }
    }

    function flush(force) {
      if (!q.length) return;
      const take = force ? q.splice(0, q.length) : q.splice(0, Math.max(1, opts.batchSize));
      sendBatch(take);
      if (q.length) schedule();
    }

    function schedule() {
      clearTimeout(timer);
      timer = setTimeout(() => flush(false), opts.batchDelay);
    }

    return {
      // Prebid calls this once when enabled
      enableAnalytics: function(config) {
        const options = (config && (config.options || config)) || {};
        opts = Object.assign(opts, options);
        console.log('[generic] enabled', opts);
      },

      // Prebid calls this for each event: { eventType, args }
      track: function(evt) {
        const payload = {
          eventType: evt && evt.eventType,
          args: evt && evt.args,
          // Hoist labels for your server‚Äôs convenience
          labels: (evt && evt.args && evt.args.labels) || (w.pbjs && w.pbjs._analyticsLabels) || {}
        };
        q.push(payload);
        if (opts.batchSize <= 1) flush(true); else schedule();
      }
    };
  }

  w.GenericAnalyticsAdapter = GenericAnalyticsAdapter;
})(window);
</script>

Your Node server already accepts single objects or arrays, sets CORS, and hoists args.labels ‚Üí labels before writing a line per event, so this payload shape fits perfectly. server

// in genericAnalyticsAdapter.js
function GenericAnalyticsAdapter() {
  var opts = { url: '', batchSize: 1, batchDelay: 0 };
  function send(url, payload) {
    const json = JSON.stringify(payload);
    const cross = new URL(url, location.href).origin !== location.origin;
    if (!cross && navigator.sendBeacon) { navigator.sendBeacon(url, json); return; }
    fetch(url, { method:'POST', mode:'cors', credentials:'omit', body: json });
  }
  return {
    enableAnalytics(config){ opts = Object.assign(opts, config && (config.options || config)); },
    track(evt){
      const out = { eventType: evt?.eventType, args: evt?.args, labels: (evt?.args && evt.args.labels) || (window.pbjs && window.pbjs._analyticsLabels) || {} };
      send(opts.url, out);
    }
  };
}

Export a proper adapter and read evt.args.labels. Also POST to your collector.

html
<!-- vendors/genericAnalyticsAdapter.js -->
<script>
(function (w) {
  function GenericAnalyticsAdapter() {
    var opts = { url: '', batchSize: 1, batchDelay: 0 };

    function send(payload) {
      try {
        const json = JSON.stringify(payload);
        const cross = new URL(opts.url, location.href).origin !== location.origin;
        if (!cross && navigator.sendBeacon) { navigator.sendBeacon(opts.url, json); return; }
        fetch(opts.url, { method: 'POST', mode: 'cors', credentials: 'omit', body: json });
      } catch (e) { console.warn('[generic] send failed', e); }
    }

    return {
      enableAnalytics: function(config) {
        const options = (config && (config.options || config)) || {};
        opts = Object.assign(opts, options);
        console.log('[generic] enabled', opts);
      },
      // Prebid calls this with { eventType, args }
      track: function(evt) {
        const labels = (evt && evt.args && evt.args.labels) || {}; // ‚¨ÖÔ∏è Enrichment Lift labels live here
        // Keep a global for anything else on the page that wants labels
        w.pbjs = w.pbjs || {};
        w.pbjs._analyticsLabels = labels;

        const payload = { eventType: evt?.eventType, args: evt?.args, labels };
        send(payload);
      }
    };
  }

  w.GenericAnalyticsAdapter = GenericAnalyticsAdapter;
})(window);
</script>

Why: your current file only sets context.labels = event?.labels (never populated by Prebid), so it stays {}. genericAnalyticsAdapter

üîß Fix: define the adapter on window

Here‚Äôs the full working minimal file. Replace vendors/genericAnalyticsAdapter.js with:

js
(function (w) {
  function GenericAnalyticsAdapter() {
    var opts = { url: '', batchSize: 1, batchDelay: 0 };

    function send(payload) {
      try {
        const json = JSON.stringify(payload);
        const cross = new URL(opts.url, location.href).origin !== location.origin;
        if (!cross && navigator.sendBeacon) {
          navigator.sendBeacon(opts.url, json);
        } else {
          fetch(opts.url, {
            method: 'POST',
            mode: 'cors',
            credentials: 'omit',
            body: json
          });
        }
      } catch (e) {
        console.warn('[generic adapter] send failed', e);
      }
    }

    return {
      enableAnalytics: function (config) {
        const options = (config && (config.options || config)) || {};
        opts = Object.assign(opts, options);
        console.log('[generic adapter] enabled', opts);
      },
      track: function (evt) {
        const labels = (evt && evt.args && evt.args.labels) || {};
        console.info('[generic adapter] track', evt.eventType, labels);

        w.pbjs = w.pbjs || {};
        w.pbjs._analyticsLabels = labels;

        send({ eventType: evt.eventType, args: evt.args, labels });
      },
      disableAnalytics: function () {}
    };
  }

  // ‚úÖ Set global so Prebid can call it later
  w.GenericAnalyticsAdapter = GenericAnalyticsAdapter;
})(window);
